    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leaks in HandoverPreparation and HandoverCommand functions\n\n### Summary\nThe `do_HandoverPreparation()` and `do_HandoverCommand()` functions in the LTE RRC ASN.1 message handling code were not properly freeing allocated memory, leading to memory leaks. This was causing issues when these functions were called repeatedly, resulting in increased memory consumption over time and potential instability.\n\nThe issue was identified by the presence of \"TODO: free the OCTET_STRING\" comments in the code, indicating that memory cleanup was not implemented.\n\nThis fix implements proper memory cleanup for both functions by:\n1. Adding calls to `OCTET_STRING_free()` to free OCTET_STRING buffers\n2. Adding calls to `ASN_STRUCT_FREE_CONTENTS_ONLY()` to properly free ASN.1 structures\n3. Removing the TODO comments since the memory is now properly freed\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/MESSAGES/asn1_msg.c`: \n  - Added proper OCTET_STRING buffer cleanup in `do_HandoverPreparation()`\n  - Added proper ASN.1 structure cleanup in `do_HandoverPreparation()`\n  - Added proper OCTET_STRING buffer cleanup in `do_HandoverCommand()`\n  - Added proper ASN.1 structure cleanup in `do_HandoverCommand()`\n  - Removed TODO comments about freeing OCTET_STRING\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call `do_HandoverPreparation()` function multiple times in a loop\n2. Monitor memory usage - it will continuously increase without being freed\n3. The same behavior can be observed with `do_HandoverCommand()`\n\nThe fix ensures that memory is properly freed after each function call, preventing memory leaks and maintaining stable memory usage over time.\n"
}